			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3826143">
									

<p>At first glance I was turned off by the tone, but yeah, after rereading and finishing the piece a day later, it's one of my favorites in recent months. You've done something really nice with the Dr. Wondertainment canons; I hope it sticks around. I saved a copy of the piece for myself, just in case &quot;she fails.&quot;</p>
<p>I do hear and relate to some of the complaints, though - I hope that other heads of GOIs don't become skips in and of themselves following the Scarlet King, and it does feel a bit out of character. Congratulations on coming up with such a controversial skip, at least!</p>

							</div>

								
